ObAgent: uncertain

Reason: DBs show large DbTime rises with higher Exec_Per_Sec and OS nodes report strong disk I/O anomalies (Page_pi, Disk_io_util, Disk_await), consistent with storage/IO-induced DB slowdown — but none of the allowed fault types is “disk I/O”. To disambiguate:
- check disk I/O metrics (disk_io_util, disk_await, avgqusz) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- check network retransmits/packet-loss (tcp_retransmits, if_errors) with whether_is_abnormal_metric;
- check DB connection errors/refusals (connect_failures, “too many connections”) or run a collect_trace on connection establishment.
JudgeAgent: No - The history did not produce a definitive root cause. Although DB and OS I/O anomalies (e.g. db_007 DbTime/Exec_Per_Sec at 2020-05-27 02:02:00 and db_003 DbTime at 2020-05-27 02:11:00, and node disk metrics) were observed, the agent remained 'uncertain' and did not pick a single component as the root location. The hypothesized cause is storage/disk I/O (not in the allowed set), so no allowed anomaly type was finalized, and the full required root-cause tuple (location, one allowed anomaly type, concrete allowed reason, and a single occurrence minute) was not all pinned down.

